#gender wise percentage of suicide
gper=suicide %>% select(Gender,Total)%>% group_by(Gender)%>% summarise(total_all=sum(Total))%>%mutate(rs=sum(total_all), percent=round((total_all/rs)*100))
label=c( paste(gper$Gender[1],gper$percent[1],'%',sep=''),
     paste(gper$Gender[2],gper$percent[2],'%',sep=''))
#bar plot
ggplot(gper,aes(x=Gender,y=percent,fill=Gender))+geom_bar(stat="identity")+scale_fill_manual(values=c("dodgerblue4","goldenrod3"))+geom_text(aes(label=percent))

#3d pie char
pie3D(gper$percent,labels=label,labelcex=1.1,explode=0.1,col=colr   )

#here we conclude that the male percentage is higher than the female
#age wise distribution of suicide
suicide %>% select(Gender,Age_group,Total)%>% filter(!Age_group=="0-100+")%>% group_by(Gender,Age_group)%>% summarise(atot=sum(Total))%>% 
  ggplot(aes(x=Age_group,y=atot,fill=Gender))+geom_bar(stat="identity",position="dodge")+
  scale_fill_manual(values=c("dodgerblue4","goldenrod3"))+labs(y="Count")
## `summarise()` has grouped output by 'Gender'. You can override using the `.groups` argument.

#male commmits more suicide
#pie3d
pdata=suicide %>% select(Age_group,Total)%>% filter(!Age_group=="0-100+")%>%group_by(Age_group)%>% summarise(atot=sum(Total))
pie3D(pdata$atot,labels=pdata$Age_group,explode=0.1,col=colr,
      main="Suicide and Age Groups ")

suicide%>% select(Age_group,Total)%>% filter(!Age_group=="0-100+")%>%group_by(Age_group)%>% summarise(atot=sum(Total))%>% ggplot(aes(x=Age_group,y=atot,fill=Age_group))+geom_bar(stat="identity")+
  scale_fill_manual(values=colr)+labs(y="Count")

#WE can say that age group 15-29 &30-44 commiting more suicides
#education level of suicide person
edu_type=suicide %>% filter(Type_code =="Education_Status")%>% select(Gender,Total,Type)%>% group_by(Gender,Type)%>% summarise(ttotal=sum(Total))
## `summarise()` has grouped output by 'Gender'. You can override using the `.groups` argument.
edu_type%>% ggplot(aes(x=str_sub(Type,1,15),y=ttotal,fill=Type))+geom_boxplot()+scale_fill_manual(values=colr)+theme(legend.position = "bottom",axis.text.x = element_text(angle=90))+labs(x="Education Level",y="count")

#here less the education level higher the number of suicide
#gender education level
edu_type%>% ggplot(aes(x=str_sub(Type,1,15),y=ttotal,fill=Gender))+geom_bar(stat="identity",position="fill")+scale_fill_manual(values=colr)+theme(legend.position = "bottom",axis.text.x = element_text(angle=90))+labs(x="Education Level",y="count")

#suicide person social status
soc_stat=suicide%>% filter(Type_code =="Social_Status")%>% select(Gender,Total,Type,Age_group)%>% group_by(Gender,Type,Age_group)%>% summarise(ttotal=sum(Total))
## `summarise()` has grouped output by 'Gender', 'Type'. You can override using the `.groups` argument.
soc_stat%>%ggplot(aes(x=Type,y=ttotal,fill=Type))+geom_boxplot()+scale_fill_manual(values=colr)+theme(legend.position = "bottom",axis.text.x = element_text(angle=90))+labs(x="Social Status" ,y="count")

#here more number of suicdes are married people
#stop people from marriad not possible
#proffessional profile
prof_p=suicide%>% filter(Type_code =="Professional_Profile")%>% select(Gender,Total,Type,Age_group)%>% group_by(Gender,Type,Age_group)%>% summarise(ttotal=sum(Total))
## `summarise()` has grouped output by 'Gender', 'Type'. You can override using the `.groups` argument.
prof_p%>% ggplot(aes(x=str_sub(Type,1,20),y=ttotal,fill=Gender))+geom_bar(stat="identity",position="fill")+scale_fill_manual(values=colr)+theme(legend.position = "bottom",axis.text.x = element_text(angle=90))+labs(x="Social Status",y="Percent")

#here people female who are housewife having high number of suicide
#also male having self employed or bussines having high suoicide
prof_p%>%ggplot(aes(x=Type,y=ttotal,fill=Type))+geom_bar(stat="identity")+scale_fill_manual(values=colr)+
  theme(legend.position = "none",axis.text.x = element_text(angle=90))+labs(x="Professional Profile" ,y="count")

#also we can say that housewife and farming&agriculture activity have more suicide
#mean adopted way of attempting suicide  suicide reason
mean_ad=suicide %>% filter(Type_code =="Means_adopted") %>%group_by(Type,Gender,Age_group)%>%summarize(mtot=sum(Total))
## `summarise()` has grouped output by 'Type', 'Gender'. You can override using the `.groups` argument.
mean_ad%>%ggplot(aes(x=Type,y=mtot,fill=Gender))+geom_bar(stat="identity",position="dodge")+scale_fill_manual(values=colr)+theme(legend.position = "bottom",axis.text.x = element_text(angle=90))+labs(x="Means Adopted",y="Count")

#people attempting suicide by hanging
#people commiting suicide by hanging and consuming insecticide
mean_ad%>%ggplot(aes(x=Type,y=mtot,fill=Age_group))+geom_bar(stat="identity",
position="dodge")+scale_fill_manual(values=colr)+theme(legend.position = "bottom",axis.text.x = element_text(angle=90))+labs(x="Means Adopted",y="Count")

#again the age group 30-44 and 15-29 having high number of suicide
#cause why people attempt suicide
cause=suicide%>% filter(Type_code =="Causes")%>% group_by(Type,Gender,Age_group)%>%summarise(ctot=sum(Total))
## `summarise()` has grouped output by 'Type', 'Gender'. You can override using the `.groups` argument.
cause%>%ggplot(aes(x=Type,y=ctot,color=Gender))+geom_point()+scale_color_manual(values=colr)+theme(legend.position = "bottom",axis.text.x = element_text(angle=65,vjust=0.5))+labs(x="Causes",y="Count")

#family problem and bankruptcy or sudden change in economic status are main 
#problem suicide reason
#also prolonged illness and paralysis is one of the reason
#cause age wise reasons 
#age 0-14
age14=cause%>% filter(Age_group =="0-14" & ctot!=0)%>% ggplot(aes(x=Type,y=ctot,fill=Type))+geom_bar(stat="identity")+theme(legend.position = "none",axis.text.x = element_text(angle=90,vjust=0.5))+labs(x="Major causes-Age 0-14",y="Count")
age14

#failure in examination ans fall in social reputation
#age 15-29
age29=cause%>% filter(Age_group =="15-29" & ctot!=0)%>% ggplot(aes(x=Type,y=ctot,fill=Type))+geom_bar(stat="identity")+theme(legend.position = "none",axis.text.x = element_text(angle=90,vjust=0.5))+labs(x="Major causes-Age 15-29",y="Count")
age29

#dowry dispute and not having children
#age 30-44
age44=cause%>% filter(Age_group =="30-44" & ctot!=0)%>% ggplot(aes(x=Type,y=ctot,fill=Type))+geom_bar(stat="identity")+theme(legend.position = "none",axis.text.x = element_text(angle=90,vjust=0.5))+labs(x="Major causes-Age 30-44",y="Count")
age44

#family problems and prolonged illness mental illness
#age 44-59
age59=cause%>% filter(Age_group =="45-59" & ctot!=0)%>% ggplot(aes(x=Type,y=ctot,fill=Type))+geom_bar(stat="identity")+theme(legend.position = "none",axis.text.x = element_text(angle=90,vjust=0.5))+labs(x="Major causes-Age 45-59",y="Count")
age59

#family problems and prolonged and mental illness
#age60+
age60=cause%>% filter(Age_group =="60+" & ctot!=0)%>% ggplot(aes(x=Type,y=ctot,fill=Type))+geom_bar(stat="identity")+theme(legend.position = "none",axis.text.x = element_text(angle=90,vjust=0.5))+labs(x="Major causes-Age 60+",y="Count")
age60

#prolongeg illlnes  cancer  family problem
#selected some reasons
suicide%>% filter(Type_code=="Causes" & Type %in% c("Failure in Examination","Family Problems","Other Prolonged Illness","Unemployment","Dowry Dispute","Poverty","Insanity/Mental Illness"))%>%select(Year,Total,Type)%>% group_by(Year,Type)%>%summarise(ytot=sum(Total))%>%  ggplot(aes(x=factor(Year),y=ytot,color=Type,group=Type))+geom_line(size=1)+scale_color_manual(values=colr)+
  theme(legend.position = "bottom",axis.text.x = element_text(angle=65,vjust=0.5))+labs(x="Year",y="Count")+geom_point(size=2)
## `summarise()` has grouped output by 'Year'. You can override using the `.groups` argument.

#family problem prolonged illness sudden mental illness
#suicide during period per year
suicide$Year<-as.factor(suicide$Year)
suicide%>%select(Year,Total,Age_group) %>% group_by(Year,Age_group) %>% summarise(total=sum(Total))%>%ggplot(aes(x=Year,y=total,group=Age_group,fill=Age_group))+
  geom_area()+scale_fill_manual(values=colr)
## `summarise()` has grouped output by 'Year'. You can override using the `.groups` argument.

#during period 2001-2012 15-45 age people suicide more
#highest ranked states number of suicide
high_state=suicide%>%filter(!State %in% c("Total (All India)","Total (States)","Total (Uts)"))%>% select(State,Year,Total) %>% group_by(State)%>% summarise(tot=sum(Total)) %>% arrange(desc(tot))%>%head(10)%>%
  ggplot(aes(x=factor(State,level=State),y=tot,color=State))+geom_point(size=4)+geom_segment(aes(xend=State,y=0,yend=tot),size=2)+theme(legend.position="none",axis.text.x=element_text(angle=90))+scale_color_manual(values=colr)+geom_text(aes(label=tot),vjust=0.3)+labs(x="State - More Suicides")
grid.arrange(high_state,nrow=1)

#maharashtra having highest number of suicide
#low ranked 
low_state=suicide%>%filter(!State %in% c("Total (All India)","Total (States)","Total (Uts)"))%>% select(State,Year,Total) %>% group_by(State)%>% summarise(tot=sum(Total)) %>% arrange(desc(tot))%>%tail(10)%>%
  ggplot(aes(x=factor(State,level=State),y=tot,color=State))+geom_point(size=4)+geom_segment(aes(xend=State,y=0,yend=tot),size=2)+theme(legend.position="none",axis.text.x=element_text(angle=90))+scale_color_manual(values=colr)+geom_text(aes(label=tot),vjust=0.3)+labs(x="State - Less Suicides")
grid.arrange(low_state,nrow=1)

#lakshdweep have lowest number of suicide
#maharashtra state
st_mh=suicide %>% filter( State=="Maharashtra" | (Type_code=="Professional_Profile" & Type=="Farming/Agriculture Activity"))%>% select(Age_group,State,Year,Total)%>% group_by(State,Year)%>% summarise(stot=sum(Total))%>% arrange(desc(stot))
## `summarise()` has grouped output by 'State'. You can override using the `.groups` argument.
st_mh%>%ggplot(aes(x=State,y=stot,group=Year,fill=Year))+geom_line()+theme(legend.position="bottom",axis.text.x=element_text(angle=90))+scale_color_manual(values=colr)
